cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.AR 

This paper discusses the use of millimeter wave technology in cellular networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of directional transmissions and the optimization of resource allocation, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper proposes a method to improve the cell search procedure using context information, which is related to system and control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of functional split between control and user plane, which is related to computer architecture (cs.AR).
